= Parameterized Snippets

Allow sending parameters to snippets


= Usage

In page 'Home':

  What's up with elephants?
  
  <r:snippet name="animal_info" animal="elephant" />
  
  And lions? What do lions do?
  
  <r:snippet name="animal_info" animal="lion" />

In snippet 'animal_info':

  <r:unless_var name="animal">
    What animal do you want info about?
    Please set the 'animal' parameter when calling this snippet!
  </r:unless_var>
  <r:if_var name="animal">
    So you want to know about <r:pluralize_and_capitalize><r:var name="animal" /></r:pluralize_and_capitalize>?
    
    <r:pluralize_and_capitalize><r:var name="animal" /></r:pluralize_and_capitalize> are fierce animals, let's hope you never meet one.
  </r:if_var>

Note: The 'pluralize_and_capitalize' tag is not included in this extension.


= Todo

  - Possibility to match a snippet parameter with a Regex, e.g. <r:if_var name="animal" matches=".*ep[h|]ant?"> (Note: this is a bad example.)

